      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Use-error modes relevant to clinical operator interaction with the CPB device and associated simulation inputs must be identified and their effect on model predictions characterized.",
      "rationale": "Use-error evaluation per IEC 62366 is addressed in a companion document. No link or reference identifier to that document is provided in this package. No use-error modes — such as perfusionist misentry of target flow rate, incorrect priming volume input, or speed dial misreading — have been characterized within the simulation validation activities. All validation results assume correctly formatted and correctly valued inputs throughout. The use-error CredibilityFactor is therefore not-assessed within this credibility package."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The hemolysis power-law model and turbulence closure must be justified for the flow regime and shear stress range encountered in the CPB pump.",
      "rationale": "Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model selected based on published validation for centrifugal blood pumps. k-omega SST turbulence closure appropriate for rotating machinery with adverse pressure gradients. Model form uncertainty bounded by turbulence model comparison study."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
